Ses01M_script01_1_F029.text: I don't see why it has to be Annie.

Ses01M_script01_1_F030.text: That's a good answer but it doesn't answer anything.  You haven't seen her since you went away to war, it's been five years.

Ses01M_script01_1_F031.text: He thinks he's coming back, Chris.  You marry that girl you're pronouncing him dead.

Ses01M_script01_1_F032.text: Do you know what that'll do to you, to your father, do you know?  I don't.

Ses01M_script01_1_F036.text: You have a business here.  I said what the hell is this?

Ses01M_script01_1_F038.text: You mean to tell me you would leave the business for this.

Ses01M_script01_1_F039.text: Well, you don't want to think like that.

Ses01M_script01_1_F040.text: All right but you don't think like that because what the hell is this all for.  This is all for you, what are we working for Chris? The whole shooting match is for you.

Ses01M_script01_1_F041.text: Well, you don't think like that.

Ses01M_script01_1_F042.text: I don't understand you, do I?

Ses01M_script01_1_M001.text: He was out here at four this morning.

Ses01M_script01_1_M002.text: I was out here at four this morning I heard a crack and I looked out the window and he was standing right over there.

Ses01M_script01_1_M003.text: I don't know.  But he went back in the kitchen and he cried.

Ses01M_script01_1_M004.text: No.  I figured I'd just let it wait.

Ses01M_script01_1_M005.text: Yeah, I could hear him crying through the floorboards in my room.

Ses01M_script01_1_M008.text: I don't know the meaning of it.  But I know we've made terrible mistake with father.

Ses01M_script01_1_M009.text: I mean, these kinds of things, man they always come back at you.  And this is definitely coming back to us.

Ses01M_script01_1_M010.text: I just--why shouldn't he walk the nights waiting for him, huh?  Do we contradict him do we say we don't have any hope any more that he's not coming back?

Ses01M_script01_1_M011.text: I don't want to argue with him, it's just for God's sake it's time he realized that no one believes with him any more.

Ses01M_script01_1_M013.text: For God's sake, three years?  Nobody comes back after three years. It's insane.

Ses01M_script01_1_M014.text: Okay, all right.  Mom, sit down.  I want to talk to you.

Ses01M_script01_1_M015.text: Yeah, okay all right, all right.  Listen, um, you know why I asked Annie here, right?

Ses01M_script01_1_M017.text: I'm going to ask her to marry me.

Ses01M_script01_1_M018.text: You know it's not just my business.

Ses01M_script01_1_M019.text: So it's okay then?  I'm just going to go ahead with it?

Ses01M_script01_1_M020.text: See.  Then it's not just my business. Sometimes you infuriate me, you know that?  You know it's just your business too if I tell father and he throws a fit about it, huh?

Ses01M_script01_1_M022.text: I don't know why it is you know every time I reach out for something I have to pull back 'cause I'm afraid it's going to hurt somebody.  All my life...

Ses01M_script01_1_M024.text: No, I wanted to get this all sorted out first.

Ses01M_script01_1_M025.text: Well, if she does then that's the end of it.  However from her letters I think she's pretty much forgotten him.

Ses01M_script01_1_M026.text: So what?  I'm just--I'm not fast with women.

Ses01M_script01_1_M028.text: I don't know, it I think of her, I grew up next to her.  She is what I think of when I think of a wife.

Ses01M_script01_1_M030.text: I've given it lots of thought.  And I keep coming back to the same thing.

Ses01M_script01_1_M031.text: When I think of a family, when I think of my future I see Annie in the center of that and you know and if that can't happen here then I'll go somewhere else.

Ses01M_script01_1_M032.text: I'll leave.  I'll get married and move somewhere else maybe New York.

Ses01M_script01_1_M034.text: Business?  The business doesn't inspire me.

Ses01M_script01_1_M035.text: Yes, yes I like it for one hour a day.  I don't care if I have to grub for money all day long when I come home I want it nice, I want a family, I want to kids and Annie is in the center of that.

Ses01M_script01_1_M038.text: Then help me stay here mom.

Ses01M_script01_1_M042.text: No, you don't.  I'm a pretty tough guy.
